WEBVTT

00:02.132 --> 00:03.133
<i>Previously on</i> Young Sheldon...

00:03.177 --> 00:05.005
What the hell's
wrong with you?

00:05.048 --> 00:06.180
MARY:
What is going on?

00:06.223 --> 00:07.964
He's dropping out
of school!
What?!

00:08.008 --> 00:09.270
It's not a big deal.

00:09.313 --> 00:11.533
You are finishing high school,
end of discussion.

00:11.576 --> 00:13.926
- It's my life.
- It's my house.

00:13.970 --> 00:16.103
If you don't go to school,
you can't live here.

00:16.146 --> 00:18.453
Hold on. We are
not kicking him out.

00:18.496 --> 00:19.541
The hell we're not.

00:19.584 --> 00:21.325
I'll pack right now.

00:21.369 --> 00:23.284
Stop. You don't have to go.

00:23.327 --> 00:26.026
Yes, he does.
My house, my rules.

00:28.158 --> 00:32.293
ADULT SHELDON: <i>
I've always had a curious
affinity for Laundromats. </i>

00:32.336 --> 00:34.469
<i>Perhaps it's the rows
of mechanical devices </i>

00:34.512 --> 00:36.471
<i>dedicated to a cleaner world.</i>

00:36.514 --> 00:38.603
<i>Or maybe it's
the hypnotic rotation </i>

00:38.647 --> 00:41.389
<i>of spinning clothes
on their sudsy journey </i>

00:41.432 --> 00:44.000
<i>to a fluffy, stain-free future.</i>

00:44.044 --> 00:46.002
<i>Mmm, look at 'em.</i>

00:46.046 --> 00:47.308
<i>Where was I?</i>

00:47.351 --> 00:49.223
<i>Oh, yes. Laundromats.</i>

00:49.266 --> 00:51.225
<i>My meemaw also loved them,</i>

00:51.268 --> 00:54.271
<i>but for an entirely
different reason. </i>

00:54.315 --> 00:56.317
♪

01:00.060 --> 01:01.670
Banana, banana...

01:02.714 --> 01:04.673
Whoo!
[laughing]

01:04.716 --> 01:06.501
<i>Personally,
I don't care for bananas. </i>

01:06.544 --> 01:08.068
<i>It's a texture thing.</i>

01:09.199 --> 01:11.332
- There you go.
- Oh, big night.

01:11.375 --> 01:12.507
Yep.

01:12.550 --> 01:14.161
You can just put it on my tab.

01:14.204 --> 01:16.467
Actually,
I'm gonna need you to cash out.

01:16.511 --> 01:19.992
How come?
I'm, uh, fixin'
to close up for good.

01:20.036 --> 01:21.255
What? Why?

01:21.298 --> 01:23.213
Gonna spend more time
with the grandkids.

01:23.257 --> 01:24.954
I got grandkids, too.

01:24.997 --> 01:26.956
Why do you think
I'm here so much?

01:26.999 --> 01:29.698
[chuckles]
So who's gonna take
over this place?

01:31.091 --> 01:34.137
Guess what,
I'm buying a Laundromat.

01:34.181 --> 01:37.097
Uh, I don't know how to react.

01:37.140 --> 01:38.924
Is that good news?

01:38.968 --> 01:40.709
Oh, yeah.

01:41.144 --> 01:42.624
Laundromat.

01:42.667 --> 01:44.234
Cool.

01:45.279 --> 01:47.759
♪ Nobody else
is stronger than I am ♪

01:47.803 --> 01:51.111
♪ Yesterday I moved a mountain

01:51.154 --> 01:53.939
♪ I bet I could be your hero

01:53.983 --> 01:56.899
♪ I am a mighty little man

01:56.942 --> 01:58.944
♪ <i>I am a mighty little man.</i> ♪

02:03.993 --> 02:05.516
SHELDON: <i>
Fun fact--</i>

02:05.560 --> 02:07.431
did you know the knife goes
on the right because it was

02:07.475 --> 02:09.477
the first utensil, and
most people are right-handed?

02:09.520 --> 02:12.132
Did you know I set the table
and no one said thank you?

02:12.175 --> 02:14.134
No one thanked me
for my fun fact.

02:14.177 --> 02:15.178
[door shuts]
You don't hear me
complaining.

02:15.222 --> 02:17.267
Hey.

02:18.268 --> 02:20.140
What are you doing here?

02:20.749 --> 02:22.533
Just thought I could
have dinner with y'all.

02:22.577 --> 02:23.665
Of course you can.

02:23.708 --> 02:25.536
I'm sorry, do you live here?

02:25.580 --> 02:27.234
Just forget it.

02:27.277 --> 02:28.800
- No. Stay.
- Mary...

02:28.844 --> 02:30.585
He can have dinner with us.

02:31.586 --> 02:32.891
Fine.

02:32.935 --> 02:34.415
Sit.

02:35.372 --> 02:37.200
I'll get you a plate.

02:39.463 --> 02:41.378
So, <i>do</i> you still live here?

02:41.422 --> 02:42.727
I don't know.

02:42.771 --> 02:44.251
Of course you do.

02:44.294 --> 02:45.252
You go back to school?

02:45.295 --> 02:46.253
[scoffs]
No.

02:46.296 --> 02:47.819
It sounds like
you don't live here.

02:47.863 --> 02:50.561
He's our son. We are
not kicking him out.
He wants

02:50.605 --> 02:52.694
to be an adult,
he can pay for his own place.

02:52.737 --> 02:54.174
That was my plan.

02:54.217 --> 02:56.393
Okay, what if he
pitches in here?

02:56.437 --> 02:57.699
Like what, rent?

02:57.742 --> 02:59.614
Yes. You would
do that, right?

02:59.657 --> 03:01.616
I guess so.

03:01.659 --> 03:03.705
Sounds like someone needs
a rental agreement.

03:03.748 --> 03:05.750
I'll go get my legal pad.

03:07.665 --> 03:10.625
Pay to live here?
We don't even have a pool.

03:12.801 --> 03:17.197
So, there's a secret back room
at the Laundromat

03:17.240 --> 03:19.111
where you gamble?

03:19.155 --> 03:21.201
- Yeah.
- And you never told me?

03:21.244 --> 03:22.941
Well, this is how secrets work.

03:22.985 --> 03:24.987
Uh-huh. What else
aren't you telling me?

03:25.030 --> 03:27.511
Let me explain secrets.

03:27.555 --> 03:29.905
Uh, okay, just give me a sense

03:29.948 --> 03:32.124
of how illegal this is.

03:32.168 --> 03:33.778
Who says it's illegal?

03:33.822 --> 03:35.127
Well, why is it a secret?

03:35.171 --> 03:36.999
Okay, it's illegal.

03:37.042 --> 03:38.870
But these places
have been around for years.

03:38.914 --> 03:41.960
Nobody gets hurt,
the cops don't care.

03:42.004 --> 03:44.659
I-I thought you liked being
retired-- now you want to be

03:44.702 --> 03:45.921
a business owner?

03:45.964 --> 03:48.184
It's not as much as fun
as I make it look.

03:48.228 --> 03:49.794
[chuckles]:
Listen,

03:49.838 --> 03:52.536
I've been gambling my whole life

03:52.580 --> 03:53.972
and losing
to the house.

03:54.016 --> 03:59.021
This is my chance
to be the house.

04:00.022 --> 04:02.546
You go to prison,
I ain't waitin' for you.

04:02.590 --> 04:05.288
You really have the energy
to find a new girlfriend?

04:06.333 --> 04:07.812
I'll wait.

04:07.856 --> 04:09.249
[chuckles]

04:09.292 --> 04:10.989
Okay, so we've agreed
on monthly rent.

04:11.033 --> 04:13.122
Should we talk utilities?

04:13.165 --> 04:14.732
Why do I got to pay
for that stuff?

04:14.776 --> 04:16.821
'Cause you use them
and they cost money.

04:16.865 --> 04:18.606
There are five of us
in the house,

04:18.649 --> 04:20.912
so I suggest he pays 20%.

04:20.956 --> 04:22.784
Although he does take a
long time drying that hair.

04:22.827 --> 04:24.002
20%'s fine.

04:24.046 --> 04:26.004
Hold on.
It takes a whole lot more water

04:26.048 --> 04:27.441
to clean you than me.

04:27.484 --> 04:29.791
Hey, watch it. I don't have
to let you live here.

04:29.834 --> 04:31.793
Let me? I'm paying
for everything.

04:31.836 --> 04:33.011
You gonna charge me
for food, too?

04:33.055 --> 04:34.448
Mm, it's not the worst idea.

04:34.491 --> 04:37.015
You know what? Maybe I
shouldn't be in this house.

04:37.059 --> 04:38.321
You said it, not me.

04:38.365 --> 04:40.149
He doesn't have
to pay for food.

04:40.192 --> 04:41.759
Meemaw does eat here for free.

04:41.803 --> 04:43.326
That's a separate problem.

04:43.370 --> 04:45.894
What if Georgie moves
into the garage?

04:45.937 --> 04:47.635
- Why?
- You'd still
be around,

04:47.678 --> 04:48.897
so Mom's happy,
but you'd be

04:48.940 --> 04:50.333
out of the house,
so Dad's happy.

04:51.769 --> 04:54.032
That could work.
What do you say?

04:54.076 --> 04:56.687
- Done.
- Done.

04:56.731 --> 04:58.036
Hold on. All my trains

04:58.080 --> 04:59.342
and science equipment
are in the garage.

04:59.386 --> 05:00.778
Where would they go?

05:00.822 --> 05:01.953
Easy. I take Georgie's room.

05:01.997 --> 05:03.607
All your crap goes in your room.

05:03.651 --> 05:06.175
That's a big change.
I need to think about this.

05:06.218 --> 05:07.350
Mom?

05:07.394 --> 05:09.178
Honey, it does make sense.

05:09.221 --> 05:11.354
You two are getting older.

05:11.398 --> 05:13.835
I don't even have hair
on my legs yet. What's the rush?

05:13.878 --> 05:15.619
Let's just put this down
for a few days.

05:15.663 --> 05:17.752
Why? 'Cause you don't want
to hear him complain?

05:17.795 --> 05:18.927
Bingo.

05:21.408 --> 05:24.106
♪

05:25.107 --> 05:26.238
Hey, Dale.

05:26.282 --> 05:27.762
Hey, Jake.

05:27.805 --> 05:29.894
Good to see you.
Hey, thanks for coming out.

05:29.938 --> 05:31.853
My pleasure.
Could I get a beer?

05:32.897 --> 05:34.899
You arrest anybody fun lately?

05:34.943 --> 05:36.074
A party clown.

05:36.118 --> 05:38.381
But what he was
doing was not fun.

05:38.425 --> 05:40.122
Do I want to know?

05:40.165 --> 05:42.080
Not if you want
to sleep tonight.

05:42.124 --> 05:43.125
Huh.

05:43.168 --> 05:44.256
What's up with you?

05:44.300 --> 05:45.780
Still dating that Connie?

05:45.823 --> 05:47.259
Yeah. Oh, yeah.

05:47.303 --> 05:49.392
Actually, that's what
I wanted to talk to you about.

05:49.436 --> 05:51.742
Oh-oh. I can check into things,

05:51.786 --> 05:55.224
but if you think she's lying,
she probably is.

05:55.267 --> 05:56.878
No, no, that's not it.

05:56.921 --> 05:59.663
Oh. Well,
still good life advice.

05:59.707 --> 06:01.273
Well, what do you know

06:01.317 --> 06:03.885
about these backroom
slot machine places?

06:03.928 --> 06:07.236
Why? You thinking of
putting one in your store?

06:07.279 --> 06:08.411
No. Uh-uh.

06:08.455 --> 06:10.370
No, actually,
I'm asking for Connie,

06:10.413 --> 06:12.154
'cause she's kind of interested.

06:12.197 --> 06:14.156
Hmm. Those places are harmless.

06:14.199 --> 06:15.810
We look the other way.

06:15.853 --> 06:16.985
Well, that's good to know.

06:17.899 --> 06:20.945
So what other laws
are okay to break?

06:20.989 --> 06:22.991
Not hiding drugs
in your keister.

06:23.034 --> 06:24.819
What was that clown thinking?

06:25.863 --> 06:28.126
When they found it,
did confetti shoot out?

06:28.170 --> 06:29.867
[both laugh]

06:31.173 --> 06:33.697
Sheldon, come on,
I need my own space.

06:33.741 --> 06:35.177
But we've always shared a room.

06:35.220 --> 06:36.744
I'm a young lady now.

06:36.787 --> 06:38.136
You seem the same to me.

06:38.180 --> 06:39.964
I have a training bra.

06:40.008 --> 06:42.445
When you complete your training,
get back to me.

06:42.489 --> 06:44.447
You know you want
privacy, too.

06:44.491 --> 06:46.362
I suppose it would be nice

06:46.406 --> 06:49.278
to have all my trains
and science equipment in here.

06:49.321 --> 06:51.367
Great. It's settled.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.717
It would be like
my Fortress of Solitude.

06:53.761 --> 06:54.979
Good for you.

06:55.023 --> 06:57.852
- Or my Bat Cave.
- Shh!

06:57.895 --> 06:59.331
Although I don't care for caves.

06:59.375 --> 07:00.724
Or bats.

07:00.768 --> 07:02.204
I suppose
Fortress of Solitude...

07:02.247 --> 07:02.857
I'm gonna choke
you with my bra.
Good night.

07:09.907 --> 07:11.779
[TV playing quietly]

07:16.871 --> 07:18.829
Want some help?

07:18.873 --> 07:20.440
You gonna charge me money?

07:20.483 --> 07:22.050
Never mind.

07:38.240 --> 07:39.807
Any chance this could wait
till halftime?

07:39.850 --> 07:42.331
I'll be done in a second.

07:45.073 --> 07:47.075
[crowd cheering on TV]

07:51.079 --> 07:52.254
ANNOUNCER:
Touchdown!

07:55.562 --> 07:57.128
- What are you doing?
- Moving my stuff.

07:57.172 --> 07:59.522
But we haven't discussed
who gets what yet.

07:59.566 --> 08:02.220
I get my stuff.
You get your stuff. Done.

08:02.264 --> 08:03.439
There's community property.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.528
We've lived together
for over ten years.

08:05.572 --> 08:07.878
In some states,
we'd be considered married.

08:07.922 --> 08:10.054
- Gross.
- I don't make the rules.
I just know them all.

08:10.098 --> 08:12.883
[sighs]
What do I have to do
to get this over with?

08:12.927 --> 08:15.233
We just need to agree
upon who gets which items.

08:15.277 --> 08:19.368
Fine. As my farewell gift to
you, let's do your dumb thing.

08:19.411 --> 08:21.239
See, when you're mean and nice
at the same time,

08:21.283 --> 08:22.371
it's confusing.

08:22.414 --> 08:23.807
Too bad, doofus.

08:23.851 --> 08:25.287
Better, thank you.

08:27.550 --> 08:29.421
Okay, thanks.
I'll see you in a bit.

08:29.465 --> 08:32.816
Chet's gonna swing by
and finalize the deal.

08:32.860 --> 08:34.035
Wait, he's coming over here?

08:34.078 --> 08:35.384
Yeah. Why?

08:35.427 --> 08:37.952
Well, this is
a very shady transaction.

08:37.995 --> 08:40.563
I mean, it should be
taking place under a bridge

08:40.607 --> 08:43.087
or in a parking lot somewhere.

08:43.131 --> 08:45.176
I'm handing him
a cashier's check.

08:45.220 --> 08:47.265
He's giving me the keys.

08:47.309 --> 08:49.006
He's gonna know where you live.

08:49.050 --> 08:51.574
I'm in the phone book.
I'm not hard to find.

08:51.618 --> 08:53.097
Well, what if
he grabs the check

08:53.141 --> 08:55.099
and just skedaddles
out of here?

08:55.143 --> 08:56.318
He's our age.

08:56.361 --> 08:58.407
He isn't skedaddling
anywhere.

08:58.450 --> 09:00.017
Ah, whatever you say.

09:00.061 --> 09:03.325
Are you disappointed this isn't
more like some old cop show?

09:03.368 --> 09:05.849
I loved <i>Rockford Files.</i>

09:05.893 --> 09:07.895
Well, I tell you what,
when he gets here,

09:07.938 --> 09:09.200
you're my muscle.

09:09.244 --> 09:12.290
If anything goes sideways,
you jump in.

09:12.334 --> 09:15.119
See, now you're talking.

09:15.163 --> 09:17.557
I'll stand behind you
and I'll crack my knuckles.

09:17.600 --> 09:19.167
With your arthritis?

09:19.210 --> 09:21.473
It's only bad when it rains.

09:21.517 --> 09:25.956
Next, one Timex brand
alarm clock.

09:26.000 --> 09:27.871
It's yours.

09:27.915 --> 09:30.004
Are you sure? It has a stylish
faux-wood finish.

09:30.047 --> 09:32.484
- Fine, I'll take it.
- Aw.

09:32.528 --> 09:34.312
- So you want it?
- Yes.

09:34.356 --> 09:36.924
- It's yours.
- Thank you.

09:39.056 --> 09:42.320
Next, one useful yet educational
map of the world trash can.

09:42.364 --> 09:43.626
I know what you're doing.

09:43.670 --> 09:45.585
Yes, I'm being thorough
about these things

09:45.628 --> 09:47.195
so we don't fight about them
down the line.

09:47.238 --> 09:48.500
What you're doing is
dragging this out

09:48.544 --> 09:49.937
because you don't
want me to leave.

09:49.980 --> 09:52.026
No, I'm not.
Yes, you are.

09:52.069 --> 09:54.332
Do you know the phrase
"pish posh"?

09:54.376 --> 09:56.030
No, and I don't want to.

09:56.073 --> 09:57.553
It's British, and it's used

09:57.597 --> 09:59.511
when someone's opinions
are absurd.

09:59.555 --> 10:01.296
And you're forcing me
to use it.

10:01.339 --> 10:02.645
Pish posh!

10:04.255 --> 10:05.256
Or, more authentically,

10:05.300 --> 10:06.344
[English accent]:
pish posh!

10:06.388 --> 10:07.650
I'm done.

10:07.694 --> 10:09.609
I know what's mine,
and I'm taking it.

10:09.652 --> 10:11.611
ADULT SHELDON: <i>
One day she said the same thing</i>

10:11.654 --> 10:13.177
<i>to her first husband.</i>

10:13.221 --> 10:16.224
<i>I like to think I prepared her
for that moment. </i>

10:17.442 --> 10:20.271
So I'm thinking dark red,
like a speakeasy.

10:20.315 --> 10:23.057
And maybe a little bar
in the corner.

10:23.100 --> 10:24.406
Well, you're gonna need
a liquor license.

10:24.449 --> 10:27.191
Oh, right. 'Cause I don't want
to break the law

10:27.235 --> 10:30.020
in my illegal gambling room.

10:30.064 --> 10:33.371
Over here is my bedroom area,
for sleeping and whatnot.

10:33.415 --> 10:34.721
That's my gym.

10:34.764 --> 10:38.028
And last but not least,
kitchen and bathroom.

10:38.072 --> 10:40.378
Georgie, do not use
that sink as a bathroom.

10:40.422 --> 10:42.642
Relax. Just number one.

10:44.295 --> 10:46.384
There you go.

10:46.428 --> 10:48.386
Okay, these posters go
on that wall.

10:48.430 --> 10:49.997
That poster goes
over the bed.

10:50.040 --> 10:51.563
[scoffs]
I'm not your moving man.

10:51.607 --> 10:54.218
You're right, I'm growing up.

10:54.262 --> 10:57.134
Guess I can't be
Daddy's little girl forever.

10:58.440 --> 11:00.398
Which one goes over the bed?

11:00.442 --> 11:01.748
Um, New Kids.

11:01.791 --> 11:04.402
First thing I'm gonna do is
get better chairs.

11:04.446 --> 11:07.710
If people are comfy, they'll
stay longer and spend more.

11:07.754 --> 11:10.017
Well, what if it's
someone's lucky chair?

11:10.060 --> 11:12.323
They're gambling in the back
of a Laundromat.

11:12.367 --> 11:15.109
Does that sound lucky to you?

11:15.152 --> 11:17.241
I'm thinking I'll put the flag
over that window

11:17.285 --> 11:18.416
for, you know, privacy.

11:18.460 --> 11:20.680
If you want, I could
sew some curtains,

11:20.723 --> 11:22.116
make it look homey.

11:22.159 --> 11:24.422
Nice. Girls will
eat that up.

11:24.466 --> 11:25.685
Flag is fine.

11:36.043 --> 11:37.174
[knock on door]

11:40.351 --> 11:43.137
Well, you been busy.
Yes.

11:43.180 --> 11:45.705
You get this in here
all by yourself?
Yes.

11:45.748 --> 11:48.142
How?
Science.

11:48.185 --> 11:49.709
Well, it looks good.

11:49.752 --> 11:52.146
I know. Now trains will be
the last thing I see

11:52.189 --> 11:53.364
before I go to sleep,

11:53.408 --> 11:54.583
and the first thing I see
when I wake up.

11:54.626 --> 11:55.715
Great.

11:55.758 --> 11:57.325
If I stir in
the middle of the night,

11:57.368 --> 11:58.369
you know what I'll see?

11:58.413 --> 12:01.068
Trains?
Trains.

12:03.548 --> 12:06.638
Well... as long as you're happy.

12:06.682 --> 12:08.510
Oh, I'm happy.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.170
Hey.

12:17.214 --> 12:19.477
You might want to
- check in on Sheldon.
- Is he okay?

12:19.521 --> 12:22.045
Well, he was smiling.

12:22.089 --> 12:23.655
Smiling how?

12:24.569 --> 12:26.354
Oh, boy.

12:33.796 --> 12:35.363
Hey. Dinner's ready.

12:35.406 --> 12:37.495
I'll eat later.
I have to finish this.

12:39.802 --> 12:42.892
I made spaghetti with
hot dogs cut up in it.

12:42.936 --> 12:45.112
I even made sure
that every piece is

12:45.155 --> 12:47.070
the exact same size.

12:47.114 --> 12:48.898
Some things are more important
than the width

12:48.942 --> 12:50.030
of a hot dog slice.

12:50.073 --> 12:52.815
And I wish I'd
known that sooner.

12:52.859 --> 12:55.775
So, you okay?

12:55.818 --> 12:57.777
Why wouldn't I be okay?

12:57.820 --> 13:00.736
Well, there's a lot
of change going on.

13:00.780 --> 13:02.216
I know that's not
your favorite.

13:02.259 --> 13:03.783
Where is that
railroad crossing?

13:03.826 --> 13:05.785
Would you like to eat in here?

13:05.828 --> 13:07.308
I'll make you a plate.

13:07.351 --> 13:08.526
I have to find that sign.

13:08.570 --> 13:10.224
It should be in this box.
Where is it?

13:15.446 --> 13:17.840
I can't find
my railroad crossing sign.

13:17.884 --> 13:19.581
Hey, how about knocking?

13:19.624 --> 13:21.452
Sorry, I've never had to knock
on that door before.

13:21.496 --> 13:22.714
Well, now you do.

13:22.758 --> 13:24.455
[grunts] I need
the crossing sign

13:24.499 --> 13:25.761
for my train set.
Have you seen it?

13:25.805 --> 13:28.590
No, and I've got company
coming soon.

13:28.633 --> 13:30.853
Perfect. An extra set of
eyes will be helpful.

13:30.897 --> 13:32.289
It's a girl, and you need
to get out of here.

13:32.333 --> 13:33.769
I'm not leaving
until I find it.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.902
Is this really
about some dumb sign,

13:35.945 --> 13:38.774
or is about you being scared
to have a room to yourself?

13:38.818 --> 13:40.863
That sign has been
there for as long as

13:40.907 --> 13:42.734
I've had that railroad set.

13:42.778 --> 13:44.780
It may seem insignificant
to you, but I need it.

13:44.824 --> 13:47.565
Everyone only cares
about themselves.

13:47.609 --> 13:49.219
You're happy because
you got the garage,

13:49.263 --> 13:50.742
Missy's happy because
she has her own room,

13:50.786 --> 13:52.744
but no one cares about
my problems.

13:52.788 --> 13:54.746
I'll help you look.

13:54.790 --> 13:56.661
Just forget it.

13:58.925 --> 14:02.189
ADULT SHELDON: <i>
As I struggled, my meemaw
began to realize </i>

14:02.232 --> 14:03.799
<i>the problem with running
a gambling den </i>

14:03.843 --> 14:05.627
<i>in the back of a Laundromat was</i>

14:05.670 --> 14:07.498
<i>it's still connected
to a Laundromat. </i>

14:07.542 --> 14:09.805
I put five pairs
of undies in here,

14:09.849 --> 14:11.459
and now there are four.

14:11.502 --> 14:13.330
Your machine ate my undies.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.332
There's a lost and found box
right over there in the corner.

14:15.376 --> 14:16.464
Just take all you want.

14:16.507 --> 14:18.814
I don't want
a stranger's undies.

14:18.858 --> 14:21.817
Then let's find
your precious undies.

14:21.861 --> 14:24.689
Look how many rhinestones
fell off in the dryer.

14:26.387 --> 14:28.824
It says right here
"do not tumble dry."

14:28.868 --> 14:30.913
No label's gonna tell me
what to do.

14:30.957 --> 14:33.655
I am not in the mood
for Texas right now.

14:33.698 --> 14:34.830
What do you want from me?

14:34.874 --> 14:37.311
Well, what size is yours?

14:38.355 --> 14:39.530
No!

14:52.761 --> 14:56.069
Finally the fun begins.

14:59.899 --> 15:01.030
What's going on?

15:01.988 --> 15:04.686
Are you Connie Tucker?

15:04.729 --> 15:07.297
Well, this sucks.

15:10.605 --> 15:14.826
[train whistles blow]

15:17.742 --> 15:19.527
Next stop, Medford.

15:19.570 --> 15:21.964
That won't be necessary.
Keep going.

15:22.008 --> 15:24.532
But, sir, your family's
waiting to board.

15:24.575 --> 15:26.012
I'm aware. Drive on.

15:26.055 --> 15:27.578
But, sir...

15:27.622 --> 15:29.537
I don't need them.
I'm fine on my own.

15:29.580 --> 15:32.453
Do not stop this train.

15:33.889 --> 15:36.892
[whistles blowing]

15:38.894 --> 15:41.288
- Turn it off.
- No.

15:41.331 --> 15:43.855
I've been listening to it
for an hour; turn it off.

15:43.899 --> 15:45.857
It's my room, I can
do what I want.

15:45.901 --> 15:48.382
Oh, really? Let's see
how you like it.

15:48.425 --> 15:50.862
♪ All for love

15:50.906 --> 15:52.734
♪ I love it when
we're together ♪

15:52.777 --> 15:55.606
♪ Girl, I need you forever...

15:55.650 --> 15:58.000
[train whistle blowing]

15:58.044 --> 15:59.915
What the hell's going on?!

15:59.959 --> 16:01.569
Missy's trying to annoy me.

16:01.612 --> 16:03.875
'Cause he won't turn
his stupid train off.

16:03.919 --> 16:06.574
You two are unbelievable.
Everything off.

16:06.617 --> 16:08.445
- But he started it.
- Now!

16:08.489 --> 16:11.579
♪ Knight in shining armor,
I will be your... ♪

16:11.622 --> 16:15.452
I thought y'all looked
the other way.

16:15.496 --> 16:18.020
We do, but I'm running
for sheriff,

16:18.064 --> 16:20.457
and this will make
my campaign pop.

16:20.501 --> 16:22.503
But you and Dale are buddies.

16:22.546 --> 16:25.375
That's why
I'm not arresting you.

16:25.419 --> 16:27.638
Hey, get one with me in it.

16:28.639 --> 16:30.424
[shutter clicks]

16:32.948 --> 16:34.776
So you gonna sell the place?

16:34.819 --> 16:36.952
No.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.998
Instead of crime boss,
you're gonna be

16:39.041 --> 16:40.782
a laundry boss.

16:40.825 --> 16:42.436
Well, I guess that's
just as cool.

16:42.479 --> 16:44.438
I'm gonna open my game room.

16:44.481 --> 16:46.048
How?

16:46.092 --> 16:47.093
I don't know.

16:47.136 --> 16:49.356
Move to a new location?

16:49.399 --> 16:51.053
I don't know!

16:51.097 --> 16:52.185
What about the Laundromat?

16:52.228 --> 16:54.187
Keep asking questions,
see what happens.

16:55.188 --> 16:57.190
- Last one.
- What?

16:57.233 --> 17:00.193
How'd you get so pretty?

17:02.064 --> 17:04.936
I hate you.

17:04.980 --> 17:07.200
I like you.

17:11.291 --> 17:12.988
ADULT SHELDON: <i>
There were plenty of reasons</i>

17:13.032 --> 17:15.251
<i>to be happy my sister
moved out. </i>

17:15.295 --> 17:19.429
<i>She snored, she teased me.</i>

17:19.473 --> 17:21.692
<i>She left her dirty clothes
everywhere. </i>

17:24.695 --> 17:28.395
<i>Clearly, I was better off
without her. </i>

17:28.438 --> 17:30.614
[knock on door]

17:36.055 --> 17:37.491
Can I sleep on your floor?

17:37.534 --> 17:39.449
Come on.

17:49.111 --> 17:50.069
ADULT SHELDON: <i>
I eventually made my peace</i>

17:50.112 --> 17:51.722
<i>with having a room to myself.</i>

17:51.766 --> 17:55.596
<i>And I was never truly alone,
thanks to my science posse: </i>

17:55.639 --> 17:59.513
<i>Stephen, Albert,
Richard and Arthur. </i>

17:59.556 --> 18:02.559
<i>But for those times when I did
need to communicate with Missy, </i>

18:02.603 --> 18:04.648
<i>we had a system.</i>

18:09.697 --> 18:11.525
What?

18:11.568 --> 18:14.528
- Just testing the system.
- You tested it yesterday.

18:14.571 --> 18:17.487
Just because it worked yesterday
doesn't mean it's working today.

18:17.531 --> 18:19.707
It's working.
Good night.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.404
Good night.
Sleep tight.

18:25.147 --> 18:27.236
[knocking on wall]

18:28.672 --> 18:30.065
What?

18:30.109 --> 18:31.545
Did you know when people say
"sleep tight,"

18:31.588 --> 18:33.199
they're referring to when
beds were made of ropes,

18:33.242 --> 18:35.070
and the tighter the rope,
the more comfortable

18:35.114 --> 18:37.246
- the bed was to sleep on?
- Cool.

18:37.290 --> 18:39.074
Bye.

18:39.118 --> 18:41.120
ADULT SHELDON: <i>
My sister wasn't always a fan</i>

18:41.163 --> 18:44.210
<i>of my informative tidbits,
so I didn't tell her </i>

18:44.253 --> 18:46.734
<i>that the entire phrase,
"Good night, sleep tight, </i>

18:46.777 --> 18:49.128
<i>don't let the bedbugs bite"
is actually </i>

18:49.171 --> 18:51.739
<i>from the 1896 book
What They Say in New England:</i>

18:51.782 --> 18:55.221
A Book of Signs, Sayings,
and Superstitions.

18:55.264 --> 18:56.657
<i>Until I told her.</i>

18:56.700 --> 18:58.615
[knocking on wall]

